<div class="entrycontent">Since I heard that BP's long term solution to the oil leak, which was going to take until August, involve drilling a second hole, I've wanted to know:<br /><br />What reason is there to believe the second hole won't blow?<br /><br /><br />(Also, why don't they put an upside down funnel over the hole, with a valve at the top, and anchor it with cables?)</div>

